      • Sax2DomHandler

        public Sax2DomHandler()
               throws javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException
        Default constructor.

        This is a shortcut for Sax2Dom(null).

        Throws:
        javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException - if the internally used DocumentBuilder cannot be created for some reason

      • Sax2DomHandler

        public Sax2DomHandler(org.w3c.dom.Node root)
               throws javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException
        Constructor which uses the specified root node as root of the document built from the SAX events.
        Parameters:
        root - the root node of the document to build; may be null to use a newly created, empty Document instance as root
        Throws:
        javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException - if the internally used DocumentBuilder cannot be created for some reason

    • Method Detail

      • getDocument

        public org.w3c.dom.Document getDocument()
        Returns the Document which holds the built DOM nodes. If no root node has been specified at construction or the specified root node was an instance of Document this method will return the root node itself, otherwise it will return the owner document of the specified root node.
        Returns:
        the Document which holds the built DOM nodes
        See Also:
        getRoot()

      • getRoot

        public org.w3c.dom.Node getRoot()
        Returns the root node specified at construction or, if none had been specified, the Document instance which has been created as the root node. The returned node is the parent of the nodes created from the SAX events.
        Returns:
        the root node specified at construction
        See Also:
        getDocument()
